This paper deals with interference channels, which are a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves analyzing the performance of communication systems (cs.COMM) in terms of diversity and multiplexing tradeoff. The use of perfect receive channel state information (CSI) is a common technique in wireless networks (cs.NI), and the paper discusses the impact of interference on the achievable tradeoff (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions a specific coding scheme (Han and Kobayashi) which is commonly used in multimedia communication (cs.MM).
